                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/798.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-17T17:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s June 16, 10 a.m. I presented matter unofficially today. The Minister
                    for Foreign Affairs regrets inability to make remittance now. He says that high
                    officials and subordinate officers of the Government have not been paid since
                    January and that the Government has not been able to pay the army promptly.
                    Income from import duties very slight since European war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
